						               													<description>An abstract game of memory and observation.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Contents: 8 round cards, 42 rectangular cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Preparing to play: Lay the 8 round cards out face down in 2 rows in between the players. Place the rectangular cards face down in a pile next to the round cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To win cards, you have to memorize the location of shapes and colors.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On your turn, turn up the top card from the draw pile, and place it next to the stack:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;bull; If this card features two colored symbols, then you must find at least one of these two symbols (same color, same shape) on one of the round cards, and to do so you turn over a single card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;bull; If you turn up a card showing 1, 2 or 3 white symbols: you must then turn up 1, 2 or 3 round cards all featuring that symbol, regardless of color.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If you turn up the correct card(s), you win the rectangular card and play again.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Otherwise leave the card on the discard pile and it is the next player&amp;rsquo;s turn.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Turn the round cards back face down in the same place.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The next player can decide to try to win the card face up on top of the discard pile (if there is one) or to turn up a new rectangular card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Only turn the round cards up to see if they feature the symbols you are looking for, and always turn them back face down at once.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;All players take advantage of each round of the game to try to memorize the symbols on the round cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends when there are no cards left in the draw pile. The player who has won the most cards wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
